protected_spaces_details.description: Provision for children and young people

description: Residential-led, mixed use redevelopment of the site to provide three new courtyard blocks, ranging from 5 storeys to 27 storeys in height comprising 807 residential units (Use Class C3), a 377sqm (GIA) childrens nursery (Use Class D1), 977sqm (GIA) of flexible retail/employment floor space (Use Classes A1, A2, and B1) with publicly accessible open space, private and shared amenity space; hard and soft landscaping; alterations to existing, and creation of new, vehicular accesses and pedestrian routes; substation; servicing bay on Lakeside Drive, car and cycle parking and associated works.
decision_agency: Old Oak and Park Royal Development Corporation
